  "description": "<i>Word Olympics</i> is a 1 - 2 player spelling word game for the 8-bit Atari.<br><br>Players have to solve anagrams by rearranging the letters present on the screen up to 8-letter words.  The player rearranges the letters by selecting them from a 3 x 3 box with the joystick, and each correct letter choice is kept on the screen.  Each correct answer causes a character to run a set distance across the top of the screen.  The first player to help their character run the length of the screen is the winner.  There a are multiple difficulty levels available.",
